00:31:04,782 --> 00:31:08,996
you really think you're playing
on the axis of the Kirk/Uhura story.

672
00:31:10,079 --> 00:31:14,542
I love the way that Spock, Kirk's
and Uhura's triangle plays,

673
00:31:14,667 --> 00:31:17,171
which is the idea that,

674
00:31:17,296 --> 00:31:20,007
you know, in a conventional movie,
Kirk is gonna get the girl.

675
00:31:20,132 --> 00:31:21,133
- And the fact that he...
- That's right.

676
00:31:21,258 --> 00:31:22,259
I love her in this shot, by the way.

677
00:31:22,384 --> 00:31:25,053
He lost her before
the movie even started.

678
00:31:25,179 --> 00:31:26,305
- That's right.
- You know, I mean, because she...

679
00:31:26,430 --> 00:31:29,432
- But you don't realise that until later.
- She's still in play, maybe, in the bar,

680
00:31:29,557 --> 00:31:32,644
but at some point in these three years,
she's fallen for Spock.

681
00:31:32,769 --> 00:31:35,439
Now, this is the same set
that we used in the <i>Kelvin.</i>

682
00:31:35,564 --> 00:31:39,984
It was redressed a little bit, but it has
much more of the submarine vibe.

683
00:31:40,109 --> 00:31:43,113
And then this was actually,
you know, part of the set.

