00:32:03,383 --> 00:32:06,428
Now, Kobayashi Maru, on a script level,

692
00:32:06,553 --> 00:32:09,765
we spent a lot of time
talking about this sequence.

693
00:32:09,890 --> 00:32:11,432
Well, the green girl
used to be a huge part of this.

694
00:32:11,557 --> 00:32:15,520
She was the one who ended up
basically planting the bug.

695
00:32:15,645 --> 00:32:16,896
Kirk had been sleeping with her

696
00:32:17,021 --> 00:32:20,483
specifically to get her to insert
the virus into the computer.

697
00:32:20,608 --> 00:32:22,819
But it somehow felt more fun
to keep it a mystery as to who did it.

698
00:32:22,944 --> 00:32:24,654
That sounds so dirty, what you just said.

699
00:32:24,779 --> 00:32:28,450
The other major change that happened
was that in its original conception,

700
00:32:28,575 --> 00:32:30,786
we didn't know
we were in the middle of a test.

701
00:32:30,911 --> 00:32:33,913
The top of, kind of, the midpoint of...

702
00:32:34,038 --> 00:32:36,916
Once Kirk went off to Starfleet
and you came back three years later,

703
00:32:37,041 --> 00:32:38,836
he was in the middle
of being the captain,

704
00:32:38,961 --> 00:32:41,255
so the intention was originally
to trick the audience into thinking

705
00:32:41,380 --> 00:32:42,839
- he had become captain.
- It felt a little bit like...

706
00:32:42,964 --> 00:32:44,173
- And we went away from that.
- Yeah.

707
00:32:44,298 --> 00:32:45,925
It just felt a little bit like
you saw it coming

708
00:32:46,050 --> 00:32:47,760
in a way that wasn't as fun.

709
00:32:47,885 --> 00:32:49,596
J.J., what about the apple?

710
00:32:50,556 --> 00:32:52,057
- I don't know. It's so funny.
- Where'd that come from.

711
00:32:52,182 --> 00:32:55,644
Someone, I can't remember who it was,
was like, "I hate it when actors eat..."

712
00:32:55,769 --> 00:32:59,314
Maybe it was Josh Reims, "I hate it
when actors eat apples in movies."

713
00:32:59,439 --> 00:33:02,108
And you were like, "We need an apple.
Let's get an apple on set."

714
00:33:02,233 --> 00:33:03,527
For some reason
while we were shooting, I thought,

715
00:33:03,652 --> 00:33:06,154
"You know what? If the guy is eating
an apple, he's so much cockier."

716
00:33:06,279 --> 00:33:09,115
I just love that this is the moment,
this whole sequence is really about that.

717
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:10,784
It's about, "This is where they cross."

718
00:33:10,909 --> 00:33:14,328
People think it's a reference
to an original <i>Trek</i> episode.

719
00:33:14,454 --> 00:33:15,788
<i>Wrath of Khan.</i>

720
00:33:15,913 --> 00:33:17,207
It's not.

721
00:33:17,332 --> 00:33:18,500
Tyler Perry, who agreed
to be in this movie,

722
00:33:18,625 --> 00:33:21,670
who had never been
in anyone else's movie,

723
00:33:21,795 --> 00:33:23,881
never been on anyone else's set,

724
00:33:24,006 --> 00:33:27,259
and he did this movie,
which I was so grateful for.

725
00:33:27,384 --> 00:33:30,636
He's such a nice guy
and a terrific actor, I thought.

726
00:33:30,761 --> 00:33:32,346
- By the way, to the right...
- I think he is really good.

727
00:33:32,472 --> 00:33:36,101
Ben Binswagner to the right,
who's the biggest <i>Trek</i> fan I've ever met,

728
00:33:36,226 --> 00:33:39,229
an old friend of mine.
So we put him in there.

729
00:33:39,354 --> 00:33:42,982
Who I also don't think had ever been in
anyone else's movie or on any other set.

730
00:33:43,107 --> 00:33:44,609
Only in Tyler Perry's film.

731
00:33:47,695 --> 00:33:48,989
This shot was fun.

732
00:33:49,114 --> 00:33:51,575
We just had these guys
just sitting on the ledge up there.

733
00:33:51,700 --> 00:33:56,538
This is one of those scenes that you
kind of, you know, eagerly await writing

734
00:33:56,663 --> 00:33:58,164
and also are terrified to write.

735
00:33:58,289 --> 00:34:01,042
There's a version, I think,
that's three times as long as this.

736
00:34:01,167 --> 00:34:02,711
- It was a much longer scene.
- There was a lot of stuff,

737
00:34:02,836 --> 00:34:04,253
- and we ended up just trimming.
- And you just realise

738
00:34:04,378 --> 00:34:06,131
what's expendable when you go to it.

739
00:34:06,256 --> 00:34:09,760
But what's so great about it,
you know, is that it's...

740
00:34:09,885 --> 00:34:13,012
Spock actually goes
to a very emotional place here.

741
00:34:13,137 --> 00:34:16,682
Even though he's presenting it
as a logical Vulcan,

742
00:34:17,768 --> 00:34:19,644
he plays the dead dad card.

743
00:34:19,769 --> 00:34:25,692
Which, you know,
is sort of a brutal piece of debating.

744
00:34:25,818 --> 00:34:26,902
Yeah.

745
00:34:27,777 --> 00:34:29,612
That was a set extension shot.

746
00:34:29,737 --> 00:34:30,280
If you look behind Spock,
the green girl is there,

747
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,949
If you look behind Spock,
the green girl is there,

748
00:34:32,074 --> 00:34:33,324
Rachel Nichols' character right there.

749
00:34:33,449 --> 00:34:37,829
She's playing angry in the sequence,
