was that we were playing Kirk too cocky.

760
00:35:04,856 --> 00:35:08,652
He hated Kirk.
His note was, "I did not like Kirk."

761
00:35:08,902 --> 00:35:11,947
And we did a pass that was literally to,
you know, answer that.

762
00:35:12,072 --> 00:35:13,574
And that included...

763
00:35:13,699 --> 00:35:16,952
- He also hated green girls, though.
- Good point.

764
00:35:17,911 --> 00:35:19,913
He also hates everybody.

765
00:35:26,961 --> 00:35:29,505
I love McCoy here.

766
00:35:31,048 --> 00:35:33,552
For canon fanatics, we always imagined
that this could have been the way

767
00:35:33,552 --> 00:35:34,760
For canon fanatics, we always imagined
that this could have been the way

768
00:35:34,887 --> 00:35:37,264
that Spock and Kirk
met in either universe.

769
00:35:37,389 --> 00:35:39,266
He always cheated
on the Kobayashi Maru,

770
00:35:39,391 --> 00:35:40,893
as known by <i>Star Trek II.</i>

771
00:35:41,018 --> 00:35:43,561
And the idea that their first meeting
was in conflict was kind of the way

772
00:35:43,686 --> 00:35:46,398
we reverse engineered what
the arc of their characters would be.

773
00:35:46,523 --> 00:35:49,233
If you met them as friends, what's
as far away as you can meet them?

774
00:35:49,358 --> 00:35:50,527
Well, you can meet them as enemies.

775
00:35:50,652 --> 00:35:52,780
That's what I liked about it,
regardless of it being <i>Star Trek,</i>

776
00:35:52,905 --> 00:35:54,239
these two characters
who meet up in this way.

777
00:35:54,364 --> 00:35:58,117
- Right.
- We shot this at a real hangar.

